-content_for(:title, 'The 24 BipolarTypes')
%p.center A BipolarType is made up of four subtypes: one from each row and column.
%p.center
  Once you have
  %span.chosen choosen a subtype,
  other subtypes in the
  %span.warning same row or column
  will become unavailable.
%p.center
  If you get stuck, you can
  =link_to "start over.", discover_path(Answer.first_path)
%h2==Subtype ##{@answer.number} of 4
%table
  %caption superego: the part of a personâ€™s mind that acts as a self-critical conscience, reflecting social standards learned from parents and teachers.
  -Attitude.all.each do |attitude|
    %tr
      -attitude.subtypes.each do |subtype|
        %td.top.quarter{:class => @answer.class(subtype)}
          %p.center=render "short", subtype: subtype
          %p.center
            -if @answer.class(subtype) == "free"
              =link_to subtype.name, discover_path(@answer.next(subtype))
            -else
              =subtype.name
